The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | H1N1 claims first live in Gujarat
                                                                                                           H1N1 claims first life in Gujarat
                                  
	Ahmedabad, Aug 9 (UNI) : An NRI Pravin Patel of Atlanta America was Gujarats first victim of the pandemic Influenza A/H1N1 flu, panicking people in the city today.              
	Health Minister Jaynarayan Vyas told UNI that Patel, who had come to visit his relatives in the citys Ranip area, died in the isolated ward of the Civil Hospital this morning.              
	The NRI was admitted along with his wife at the Civil Hospital on Friday night.              
	He said, Even though a person has died, there is no need to panic as the Government machinery is well-prepared to control the situation.              
	So far, only 52 people were suspected of N1H1 virus, of which only 13 were tested positive in Gujarat.              
	The patients are being treated at various government-run hospitals in the state, Mr Vyas said adding the government has decided to set up testing facilities at the laboratory of the B J Medical college here.              
	He said the screening of inbound passengers, which were going on at Sardar Patel International Airport here since last two months, have been intensified.                                                                                                                                             
